President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Philip D. Moeller for the position of Commissioner in the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Moeller was previously nominated by President Bush and has been serving as a Commissioner since 2006. Prior to his role in the Commission, Moeller worked as an energy policy advisor to U.S. Senator Slade Gorton, where he focused on electricity policy, energy efficiency, and other energy-related legislation. He also held positions in the Washington, D.C. offices of Alliant Energy Corporation and Calpine Corporation. Moeller was born in Chicago and raised on a ranch near Spokane, Washington. He holds a B.A. in Political Science from Stanford University.